The paper discusses a theory for describing the relation between verbs, tenses, and adjuncts in natural language texts, and how to extract temporal information from them using an abductive resolution procedure. This involves a combination of natural language processing, logic, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of first-order logic, which is relevant to the subfield of computational logic (cs.CR), and the construction of a model, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
